data.description: Introduction to economic ways of thinking about a wide range of problems and issues. Topics include consumption, production, prices, markets, finance, trade, pollution, growth, farms, taxes, and development.
data.title: INTRODUCTION TO AGRICULTURAL AND APPLIED ECONOMICS

data.description: This course explores the roles of markets, states, and civil institutions, using economic theory, computer simulations, and historical experience to better understand the forces that shape the wealth and well-being of nations and people around the world.
data.title: THE GROWTH AND DEVELOPMENT OF NATIONS IN THE GLOBAL ECONOMY
